      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I need help writing a rejection email. We had a candidate, Marcus, who made it all the way to the final interview for our Senior Dev role here in Austin. He's really talented and had great technical skills, but we decided to go with someone who had a bit more experience with our specific cloud architecture. I want the email to be professional and kind because he was a great guy, but we need to be firm that the decision is final. Can you draft something?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here's a draft rejection email that's professional, kind, and firm:\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the Senior Developer position at our Austin office. We were truly impressed by your technical skills and the enthusiasm you brought to our final interview. Unfortunately, after careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience aligns more closely with our specific cloud architecture needs.\n\nPlease know that this decision was not made lightly, and we were genuinely impressed by your qualifications and potential. You would be a great fit for many organizations, and we have no doubt that you will find a role that suits your skills and interests.\n\nWe appreciate the time and effort you invested in our interview process, and we're grateful for the opportunity to have met you. We wish you all the best in your job search and hope that our paths will cross again in the future.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\n\nI hope this draft captures the tone you're looking for. Just remember to keep it professional and kind, but firm. You want to be clear that the decision is final, but also respectful of Marcus's time and effort.",
